summary: This is a brief email from Judge Alison J. Nathan's chambers to counsel in the case US v. Maxwell (20cr330), transmitting two court orders related to a protective order and a subpoena protective order. It serves as a formal notification of the issuance of these documents.

persons.name: Alison J. Nathan
persons.context: The Honorable Judge presiding over the case US v. Maxwell (20cr330), whose chambers issued the email transmitting two court orders.

persons.name: Nathan
persons.context: Referred to in the context of the orders being issued by Judge Nathan, presiding over the case.

events.title: Issuance of Protective Orders
events.description: Judge Alison J. Nathan issued two orders: one regarding a protective order and another regarding a subpoena protective order in the case US v. Maxwell.

keyFacts: The document is an email from the chambers of Judge Alison J. Nathan regarding case 20cr330, US v. Maxwell.
Two court orders were issued on November 24, 2021: one re a protective order and another re a subpoena protective order.
The email serves as a formal notification to counsel, requesting confirmation of receipt before the orders are docketed.
